I was first elected in October 2014 on my firm opposition to the water charges and commitment to build a people-power movement to defeat them. I have used my position to make a dfference for working people since.&nbsp;
In the last Dáil term, I strongly opposed the government’s attempt to roll back Irish neutrality and join NATO. I exposed the corruption of four ministers and won a High Court case against SIPO to force them to investigate Leo Varadkar for leaking a contract.&nbsp;
